<subSubSection id="16F8653DC866FFF3FF4EFF28361AFDC2" pageId="5" pageNumber="31" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="5E5D36B6C866FFF3FF4EFF2837C1F89E" blockId="5.[151,1436,151,1222]" pageId="5" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis id="6C96EAA4C866FFF3FF4EFF283574F9B5" bold="true" box="[198,268,151,177]" pageId="5" pageNumber="31">Notes</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName id="99E24D35C866FFF3FEBAFF27363BF9B5" authorityName="Trovo, Echtern. &amp; Sano" authorityYear="2011" box="[306,579,152,177]" class="Liliopsida" family="Eriocaulaceae" genus="Paepalanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="5" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hirtellus">
<emphasis id="6C96EAA4C866FFF3FEBAFF27363BF9B5" box="[306,579,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="31">Paepalanthus hirtellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is assigned to 
<emphasis id="6C96EAA4C866FFF3FC85FF27375BF9B5" box="[781,803,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="31">P.</emphasis>
subsection 
<emphasis id="6C96EAA4C866FFF3FC34FF2730ECF9B5" box="[956,1172,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="31">Actinocephaloides</emphasis>
based mainly on its trimerous flowers and elongated stems, that are rarely branched at the base (when sterile), bearing scapes arranged in an apical inflorescence (in a single season). It is easily distinguished from the remaining species of this group by its broad leaves with cordate bases, hirtellous spathes, glabrous scapes and blackish involucral bracts. As previously discussed, the distinction between 
<emphasis id="6C96EAA4C866FFF3FC0AFE8D37E4F84F" box="[898,924,306,331]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="31">P.</emphasis>
subsection 
<taxonomicName id="99E24D35C866FFF3FBBFFE8D30D7F84F" authority="Less." authorityName="Ruhland" authorityYear="1903" box="[1079,1199,306,331]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Polyactis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Asterales" pageId="5" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6C96EAA4C866FFF3FBBFFE8D30D7F84F" box="[1079,1199,306,331]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="31">Polyactis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis id="6C96EAA4C866FFF3FB7AFE8D3174F84F" box="[1266,1292,306,331]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="31">P.</emphasis>
subsection 
<emphasis id="6C96EAA4C866FFF3FF1FFEE63517F876" box="[151,367,345,370]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="31">Actinocephaloides</emphasis>
seems ambiguous, relying on a few variable characters. Thus, it does not come to a surprise that 
<taxonomicName id="99E24D35C866FFF3FF42FE3F3531F89D" authorityName="Trovo, Echtern. &amp; Sano" authorityYear="2011" box="[202,329,384,409]" class="Liliopsida" family="Eriocaulaceae" genus="Paepalanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="5" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hirtellus">
<emphasis id="6C96EAA4C866FFF3FF42FE3F3531F89D" box="[202,329,384,409]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="31">P. hirtellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically similar to species of both groups.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5E5D36B6C866FFF3FF4EFE183617FA18" blockId="5.[151,1436,151,1222]" pageId="5" pageNumber="31">
<treatmentCitationGroup id="7EF21198C866FFF3FF4EFE183617FA18" pageId="5" pageNumber="31">
<treatmentCitation id="DF4310A7C866FFF3FF4EFE183758F8C4" author="Silveira, A. A." box="[198,800,422,448]" page=")" pageId="5" pageNumber="31" year="1928">
<taxonomicName id="99E24D35C866FFF3FF4EFE183758F8C4" authority="Silveira (1928: 176)" authorityName="Silveira" authorityPageNumber="176" authorityYear="1928" box="[198,800,422,448]" class="Liliopsida" family="Eriocaulaceae" genus="Paepalanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="5" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chrysophorus">
<emphasis id="6C96EAA4C866FFF3FF4EFE18366DF8C4" box="[198,533,423,448]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="31">Paepalanthus chrysophorus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="3A734B47C866FFF3FDADFE193758F8C4" author="Silveira, A. A." box="[549,800,422,448]" pageId="5" pageNumber="31" pagination="426" refId="ref2446" refString="Silveira, A. A. (1928) Floralia Montium, vol 1. Imprensa Official, Bello Horizonte, p. 426." type="book chapter" year="1928">Silveira (1928: 176)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</treatmentCitation>
is the species morphologically most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="99E24D35C866FFF3FA0EFE183482F8E2" authorityName="Trovo, Echtern. &amp; Sano" authorityYear="2011" class="Liliopsida" family="Eriocaulaceae" genus="Paepalanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="5" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hirtellus">
<emphasis id="6C96EAA4C866FFF3FA0EFE183482F8E2" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="31">P. hirtellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but that species has been assigned to 
<emphasis id="6C96EAA4C866FFF3FD4EFE7236A7F8E2" box="[710,735,461,486]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="31">P.</emphasis>
subsection 
<taxonomicName id="99E24D35C866FFF3FCE0FE7237AEF8E2" authority="Less." authorityName="Ruhland" authorityYear="1903" box="[872,982,461,486]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Polyactis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Asterales" pageId="5" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6C96EAA4C866FFF3FCE0FE7237AEF8E2" box="[872,982,461,486]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="31">Polyactis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Both species have an elongated stem that may ramify at the base. They also share the rigid ciliate, 
<quantity id="991A9B53C866FFF3FCF3FE4B37ACFB0A" box="[891,980,500,526]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="31" unit="cm" value="3.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="2.0">2–5 cm</quantity>
long leaves. The leaves are hairy and patent. Other similar features are found in the scapes that are glabrous. 
<taxonomicName id="99E24D35C866FFF3FC66FDA53082FB37" authorityName="Trovo, Echtern. &amp; Sano" authorityYear="2011" box="[1006,1274,538,563]" class="Liliopsida" family="Eriocaulaceae" genus="Paepalanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="5" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hirtellus">
<emphasis id="6C96EAA4C866FFF3FC66FDA53082FB37" box="[1006,1274,538,563]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="31">Paepalanthus hirtellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be easily distinguished by its broader leaves (0.5–1.0 cm) with cordate bases (vs. 
<quantity id="991A9B53C866FFF3FB9BFDFE30E6FB5F" box="[1043,1182,577,603]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="31" unit="cm" value="0.25" valueMax="0.3" valueMin="0.2">0.2–0.3 cm</quantity>
, with truncate base), shorter scapes (
<quantity id="991A9B53C866FFF3FEC5FDD735BCFB86" box="[333,452,616,642]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.35" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="5" pageNumber="31" unit="cm" value="13.5" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="12.0">12–15 cm</quantity>
vs. 
<quantity id="991A9B53C866FFF3FE7DFDD73616FB86" box="[501,622,616,642]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="31" unit="cm" value="35.0" valueMax="40.0" valueMin="30.0">30–40 cm</quantity>
), narrower capitula (
<quantity id="991A9B53C866FFF3FCEAFDD737BDFB86" box="[866,965,616,642]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="31" unit="mm" value="5.0" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="4.0">4–6 mm</quantity>
vs. 
<quantity id="991A9B53C866FFF3FC7EFDD73013FB86" box="[1014,1131,616,642]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="7.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="31" unit="mm" value="8.5" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="7.0">7–10 mm</quantity>
), longer stems (
<quantity id="991A9B53C866FFF3FAADFDD731E4FB86" box="[1317,1436,616,642]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="9.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="31" unit="cm" value="55.0" valueMax="90.0" valueMin="20.0">20–90 cm</quantity>
vs. 
<quantity id="991A9B53C866FFF3FF37FD313551FBAC" box="[191,297,654,680]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="0.2" pageId="5" pageNumber="31" unit="cm" value="16.0" valueMax="30.0" valueMin="2.0">2–30 cm</quantity>
), and blackish involucral bracts (vs dark brown). 
<taxonomicName id="99E24D35C866FFF3FCE4FD3030CCFBAC" authorityName="Silveira" authorityYear="1928" box="[876,1204,655,680]" class="Liliopsida" family="Eriocaulaceae" genus="Paepalanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="5" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chrysophorus">
<emphasis id="6C96EAA4C866FFF3FCE4FD3030CCFBAC" box="[876,1204,655,680]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="31">Paepalanthus chrysophorus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distributed in the northern Espinhaço Range in 
<collectingRegion id="9C26F854C866FFF3FD8AFD0A36D0FBCB" box="[514,680,693,719]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="5" pageNumber="31">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
, between São Gonçalo do Rio Preto and Grão-Mogol. In both localities, individuals occur on sandy-rocky soils on riverbanks. 
<taxonomicName id="99E24D35C866FFF3FC1EFD6330DAFBF1" authorityName="Trovo, Echtern. &amp; Sano" authorityYear="2011" box="[918,1186,732,757]" class="Liliopsida" family="Eriocaulaceae" genus="Paepalanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="5" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hirtellus">
<emphasis id="6C96EAA4C866FFF3FC1EFD6330DAFBF1" box="[918,1186,732,757]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="31">Paepalanthus hirtellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="99E24D35C866FFF3FB55FD6331E4FBF1" authorityName="Silveira" authorityYear="1928" box="[1245,1436,732,757]" class="Liliopsida" family="Eriocaulaceae" genus="Paepalanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="5" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chrysophorus">
<emphasis id="6C96EAA4C866FFF3FB55FD6331E4FBF1" box="[1245,1436,732,757]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="31">P. chrysophorus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are most likely allopatric in distribution.
</treatmentCitationGroup>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5E5D36B6C866FFF3FF4EFC96361AFDC2" blockId="5.[151,1436,151,1222]" pageId="5" pageNumber="31">
Another species morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName id="99E24D35C866FFF3FD7DFC963704FA46" authorityName="Trovo, Echtern. &amp; Sano" authorityYear="2011" box="[757,892,809,834]" class="Liliopsida" family="Eriocaulaceae" genus="Paepalanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="5" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hirtellus">
<emphasis id="6C96EAA4C866FFF3FD7DFC963704FA46" box="[757,892,809,834]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="31">P. hirtellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is 
<taxonomicName id="99E24D35C866FFF3FC38FC96312FFA47" authority="Silveira (1928: 180)" authorityName="Silveira" authorityPageNumber="180" authorityYear="1928" box="[944,1367,809,835]" class="Liliopsida" family="Eriocaulaceae" genus="Paepalanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="5" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lombensis">
<emphasis id="6C96EAA4C866FFF3FC38FC963032FA46" box="[944,1098,809,834]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="31">P. lombensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="3A734B47C866FFF3FBD2FC96312FFA47" author="Silveira, A. A." box="[1114,1367,809,835]" pageId="5" pageNumber="31" pagination="426" refId="ref2446" refString="Silveira, A. A. (1928) Floralia Montium, vol 1. Imprensa Official, Bello Horizonte, p. 426." type="book chapter" year="1928">Silveira (1928: 180)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
both belonging to 
<emphasis id="6C96EAA4C866FFF3FEBBFCEF3534FA6D" box="[307,332,848,873]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="31">P.</emphasis>
subsection 
<emphasis id="6C96EAA4C866FFF3FE5DFCEF36D6FA6D" box="[469,686,848,873]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="31">Actinocephaloides</emphasis>
. Similar to 
<taxonomicName id="99E24D35C866FFF3FCB3FCEF37C2FA6D" authorityName="Trovo, Echtern. &amp; Sano" authorityYear="2011" box="[827,954,848,873]" class="Liliopsida" family="Eriocaulaceae" genus="Paepalanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="5" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hirtellus">
<emphasis id="6C96EAA4C866FFF3FCB3FCEF37C2FA6D" box="[827,954,848,873]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="31">P. hirtellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="99E24D35C866FFF3FC7DFCEF30CAFA6D" authorityName="Silveira" authorityYear="1928" box="[1013,1202,848,873]" class="Liliopsida" family="Eriocaulaceae" genus="Paepalanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="5" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chrysophorus">
<emphasis id="6C96EAA4C866FFF3FC7DFCEF30CAFA6D" box="[1013,1202,848,873]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="31">P. chrysophorus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, this species has an elongated stem with ciliate, 
<quantity id="991A9B53C866FFF3FE56FCC9364DFA94" box="[478,565,886,912]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="31" unit="cm" value="3.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="2.0">2–5 cm</quantity>
long leaves. It shares the length of the spathes (
<quantity id="991A9B53C866FFF3FBE8FCC930C1FA94" box="[1120,1209,886,912]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="31" unit="cm" value="5.0" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="4.0">4–6 cm</quantity>
) and the size of the capitula (
<quantity id="991A9B53C866FFF3FE8BFC22351EFAB3" box="[259,358,925,951]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="31" unit="mm" value="5.0" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="4.0">4–6 mm</quantity>
) with the former, but 
<taxonomicName id="99E24D35C866FFF3FDECFC22369AFAB2" authorityName="Trovo, Echtern. &amp; Sano" authorityYear="2011" box="[612,738,925,950]" class="Liliopsida" family="Eriocaulaceae" genus="Paepalanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="5" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hirtellus">
<emphasis id="6C96EAA4C866FFF3FDECFC22369AFAB2" box="[612,738,925,950]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="31">P.hirtellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is readily distinguishable by its longer stems (
<quantity id="991A9B53C866FFF3FB76FC22310CFAB3" box="[1278,1396,925,951]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="9.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="31" unit="cm" value="55.0" valueMax="90.0" valueMin="20.0">20–90 cm</quantity>
vs. 
<quantity id="991A9B53C866FFF3FF1FFC7B357EFADA" box="[151,262,964,990]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.35" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="0.2" pageId="5" pageNumber="31" unit="cm" value="13.5" valueMax="25.0" valueMin="2.0">2–25 cm</quantity>
), rigid and patent leaves (vs. membranaceous and suberect leaves), abaxially hairy leaves (vs. abaxially glabrous leaves), broader leaves (0.5–1.0 cm) with cordate bases (vs. 
<quantity id="991A9B53C866FFF3FBE2FC55308AFD00" box="[1130,1266,1002,1028]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="31" unit="cm" value="0.25" valueMax="0.3" valueMin="0.2">0.2–0.3 cm</quantity>
with truncate base), glabrous scapes (vs. pilose scapes), blackish involucral bracts (vs. brown involucral bracts) and glabrous sepals of the pistillate flowers on the abaxial surfaces (vs. hairy on abaxial surfaces at apex). 
<taxonomicName id="99E24D35C866FFF3FF1FFBE035C7FD7C" authorityName="Silveira" authorityYear="1928" box="[151,447,1119,1144]" class="Liliopsida" family="Eriocaulaceae" genus="Paepalanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="5" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lombensis">
<emphasis id="6C96EAA4C866FFF3FF1FFBE035C7FD7C" box="[151,447,1119,1144]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="31">Paepalanthus lombensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known exclusively from a single collection from Pico do Itambé, without any precise information. As Pico do Itambé represents a large mountain area, it is not possible to state whether the two species occur sympatrically or not.
</paragraph>
